column48: \"hoverEvent\":{\"contents\":{\"translate\":\"+ Can teleport by holding sneak and right-clicking with nothing in the offhand\\n+ Teleport range is greatly increased in The End\\n+ Chorus fruit will teleport you over a much larger spread distance than normal\\n+ Have slightly increased block interaction range\\n- Will take damage from sources of water\"}
column55: \"hoverEvent\":{\"contents\":{\"translate\":\"+ Can jump two blocks high\\n+ Have increased movement speed\\n+ Have increased jump height and movement speed in the Faewild\\n+ Will passively gain small amounts of experience points over time \\n- Have decreased attack damage\"}
column62: \"hoverEvent\":{\"contents\":{\"translate\":\"+ Are more resilient to damage\\n+ Have immunity to Slowness
column65: Mining Fatigue and Hunger\\n+ Are unaffected by the frigid colds of Glacium\\n+ Can survive without food \\n+ Are empowered by standing in powdered snow\\n- Become weak and hungry while in hot climates\\n- Take increased damage from fire and lava\"}
column72: \"hoverEvent\":{\"contents\":{\"translate\":\"+ Have Luck x5 and Hero of the Village x5 when in the Overworld\\n+ Have no downsides\"}
column79: \"hoverEvent\":{\"contents\":{\"translate\":\"+ Hunters assimilate what they eat. Eating raw food will morph you into something resembling what you ate\\n+ Drinking milk
column80: honey or getting too hungry will de-morph you\\n- Large quantities of food are required to satisfy you each day\\n- Being morphed takes a considerable amount of effort and energy
column88: \"hoverEvent\":{\"contents\":{\"translate\":\"+ Have permanent water breathing and night vision\\n+ Have increased movement speed and mining speed while underwater or in rain\\n+ Conduit Power will regenerate you\\n- Become weak and hungry while in hot climates \\n- Have slightly decreased movement speed outside of water\"}
column95: \"hoverEvent\":{\"contents\":{\"translate\":\"+ Have permanent fire resistance and night vision \\n+ Have increased attack damage when on fire or in lava\\n+ Have increased attack damage in the nether \\n- Will take damage from sources of water\"}
column102: \"hoverEvent\":{\"contents\":{\"translate\":\"+ Can turn invisible by sneaking\\n+ Can backstab entities
column103: inflicting three times the damage when hitting an entity from behind\\n+ Have increased block interaction range\\n- Cannot turn invisible while in Sanctum\\n- Have Mining Fatigue while in Sanctum\"}
column110: \"hoverEvent\":{\"contents\":{\"translate\":\"+ Have an absorption shield that regenerates every 10 seconds \\n+ Will spread the effects of eating a notch or golden apple to nearby players \\n- The shield only works in illuminated areas
column111: when you have near full health and aren\u0027t wearing a helmet\"}
column118: \"hoverEvent\":{\"contents\":{\"translate\":\"+ Are more resilient to damage\\n+ Have slightly increased attack damage\\n+ Have slightly increased attack speed \\n- Iron golems will always be hostile\\n- Villagers will give you Bad Omen\\n- Cannot be given Hero of the Village \\n- Have permanent Bad Luck x10\"}
